This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on the evaluation of meaning representation graphs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes normalization methods for ensuring fair evaluation, which suggests that it could be relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a metric (Smatch) for evaluating the graphs, which could be relevant to the field of natural language understanding (cs.NE). Finally, the paper could also be relevant to the field of information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with the representation and evaluation of meaning in text.
